• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG – The South African Communist Party's (SACP) has announced that the party will contest future elections. The modalities of how it is to do this is yet to be clarified. The news was broken by the newly-elected second deputy general secretary of the party, Chris Mathlako. Blade Nzimande was re-elected unopposed at the congress while his deputy, Jeremy Cronin, was unavailable for re-election. The SACP resolved to hold a special national congress next year. WATCH - WATCH: SACP Congress kicks off eNCA